Description: Fragment of shoulder and handle of East Greek pottery transport amphora; very micaceous clay with some large white inclusions; residue remains inside; pre-firing graffito.
Curator's comments: Profile and clay correspond largely to Samian material, though the large inclusions are unusual. Fig remains were analysed in the interior (Stacey, R., Cartwright, C., Tanimoto, S. and Villing, A. 2010, ‘Coatings and contents: investigations of residues on four fragmentary sixth-century BC vessels from Naukratis (Egypt)’, British Museum Technical Bulletin 4, 20, fig. 1a.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JA.084)
Stacey et al 2010 / Coatings and contents: investigations of residues on four fragmentary sixth-century BC vessels from Naukratis (Egypt) (p.20, fig.1a, p.21, table.1, p.22, p.23, fig.3, p.24)
